    <section id="faq" class="faq-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">Is it safe for children to have their own crypto wallets?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Yes, when properly implemented. Our educational wallets are designed specifically for children with enhanced security features, parental controls, and strict limits. The wallets are managed through a custodial system where parents maintain ultimate oversight while children learn about digital asset management in a safe environment.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">How do the educational NFTs differ from regular cryptocurrency?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Our educational NFTs are not speculative assets. They represent verified academic achievements and have predefined educational value. They can't be sold on open markets and are designed exclusively as educational tools to incentivize learning while teaching blockchain concepts.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">What can children do with their achievement NFTs?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Children can collect their NFTs as proof of their accomplishments, display them in their digital portfolios, and exchange them for rewards within our educational ecosystem. These rewards include educational resources, special learning opportunities, and contributions toward educational savings.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">How does the verification process work?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Achievements are verified through a multi-step process. Teachers or tutors submit completed milestones, parents confirm them, and our system records these verifications on the blockchain. This creates a transparent, tamper-proof record of the child's educational journey.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-question">At what age can children start participating?</div>
                <div class="faq-answer">
                    Our program is designed for children ages 8 and up. However, the level of independence and complexity scales with age. Younger children have more parental oversight and simpler challenges, while teenagers can engage with more complex aspects of the platform.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
